@davecheney, I know about nacltest.sh. That's like all.bash. I was reporting about make.bash, which happens earlier (and is called by nacltest.sh).

You can get past the "must be bootstrapped" issue by running make.bash in the $GOROOT_BOOTSTRAP/src directory, but that doesn't feel like what we want to be doing.

I agree with Minux that there's some missing part of the cross-compilation story.
